1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sincro: wyxchari

2
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:31,039
Doctor, do something!
博士，做点什么啊！

3
00:00:31,975 --> 00:00:32,816
I'm trying to!
我正努力呢

4
00:00:46,093 --> 00:00:47,977
Everything back under control again.
一切又恢复掌控之中了

5
00:00:51,486 --> 00:00:53,567
Here, we're landing! Look!
我们快着陆了，看！

6
00:00:53,639 --> 00:00:54,566
Coming at a fair rate!
速度很平稳

7
00:00:57,149 --> 00:01:02,602
Oh, thank the lord for that. You know, Doctor,
I'll never ask you to do that again.
噢，感谢上天。博士，我再也不让你那么做了

8
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:07,938
There're must be a reason for that.
出现这个情况肯定是有原因的

9
00:01:10,869 --> 00:01:16,226
Anyway, Doctor, you... you've done it. It's Mars! It must be./
不管怎样, 博士，你...你搞定了. 到火星了！这肯定是

10
00:01:16,369 --> 00:01:18,626
You've landed the TARDIS exactly where you said you would.
你将 TARDIS 降落到了你承诺过的地方

11
00:01:43,298 --> 00:01:46,891
Hey, wait a mo! This doesn't look like Mars to me.
嘿，等一下！我觉得这里不像是火星

12
00:01:47,098 --> 00:01:48,833
How do you know? You never seen it.
你怎么知道？你又从来没见过

13
00:01:49,055 --> 00:01:53,559
No, Duchess, but I have seen pictures of the moon surface
and that's what this looks like.
是没见过，夫人．但我看过月球表面的照片，这跟那个很像啊

14
00:01:53,694 --> 00:01:55,324
That's the moon?
那是月球？

15
00:01:55,819 --> 00:01:58,523
Doctor, is it the moon?
博士，这是月球吗？

16
00:02:01,614 --> 00:02:05,554
Haha, you weren't too far out, were you?
Only two hundred million miles!
哈哈，你没有偏离多远吧，对不？不到两亿英里！

17
00:02:06,324 --> 00:02:10,752
All right, let's move on - while we can.
好啦，我们继续前进吧 - 趁着还能

18
00:02:11,995 --> 00:02:12,614
What?
什么！

19
00:02:13,207 --> 00:02:18,909
Now wait a minute! You don't expect to land us
on the moon and let us fly off just like that, do you?
等一下！你不会指望把我们拉到月球，然后就马上把我们拉走吧，是吧？

20
00:02:18,916 --> 00:02:20,254
Yeah, at least let us have a look around!
是啊，至少我们得四周转转

21
00:02:20,357 --> 00:02:24,254
That picture canna be the moon? The moon's way up in the sky.
那个镜头不可能是月球．月球正在天上呢

22
00:02:24,636 --> 00:02:25,325
Where do you think you're going?
你觉得你要去哪儿？

23
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,308
You're not going to tell us there is no shore leave?
你不会告诉我们没有上岸假期吧？

24
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:31,247
Oh please Doctor. The TARDIS isn't out of control or anything is it?
噢求你了，博士．TARDIS没有失控什么的吧？

25
00:02:31,342 --> 00:02:34,395
Oh no, no, no. Just a bumpy landing. That's all 
没没没，只是着陆有点颠簸，仅此而已

26
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:35,134
Yeah?
嘢？

27
00:02:35,375 --> 00:02:38,551
Well, if you must go ashore... only half an hour.
好吧，如果你们要上岸...只有半个小时

28
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,243
- Right. - Superb
- 好  - 太棒了

29
00:02:39,428 --> 00:02:43,881
You can't go ashore like that!
You need space suits, there's no atmosphere out there.
你们不能就这样上岸啊！你们需要太空服，外面没有空气

30
00:02:44,119 --> 00:02:45,233
Come on, there's some in the chest.
来，箱子里有几件

31
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:54,621
We'll maybe meet the old man in the moon.
也许我们能碰到月球上最老的人

32
00:02:55,474 --> 00:02:57,930
You won't meet anybody mate if you don't get some gear on.
如果你不穿上一些装备，你就碰不到任何人了

33
00:02:58,025 --> 00:02:59,991
What? Oh aye.
什么？是啊

34
00:03:11,994 --> 00:03:14,012
Come on now, lets go over here.
现在来吧，我们到这里来

35
00:03:14,448 --> 00:03:16,594
Hey, look at this.
嘿，看看这个

36
00:03:17,376 --> 00:03:18,862
Its deserted.
这里很荒凉

37
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:20,638
Yeah, I don't think I like it.
是啊，我觉得我不喜欢它

38
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,406
Look, over there.
看，那边

39
00:03:33,066 --> 00:03:34,954
I'll don't see anything.
我什么也没看见FIXME

40
00:03:35,638 --> 00:03:37,103
What did you see?
你看到了什么？

41
00:03:37,395 --> 00:03:39,744
Some sort of great glow in the sky.
天空中出现某种巨大的光圈

42
00:03:40,021 --> 00:03:43,409
Probably your eyes getting used to the lunar light.
Hey, Doctor?
也许是你的眼睛还没有适应月光，是吧，博士

43
00:03:43,732 --> 00:03:44,794
Possibly.
有可能

44
00:03:51,633 --> 00:03:54,763
Hey, what do we need this great clogs for?
嘿，我们需要这个累赘做什么？

45
00:03:55,054 --> 00:03:56,708
Try a little jump.
试着轻轻跳一下

46
00:03:57,694 --> 00:03:59,247
All right.
好啊

47
00:04:16,417 --> 00:04:20,593
Careful! One tear in that space suit and you'll suffocate.
小心点！太空服破一个口子你们就会窒息

48
00:04:20,824 --> 00:04:23,270
You never told me that you took ballet lessons, Ben.
你从来没有告诉我我你学过芭蕾，Ben

49
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:31,182
Come on, it's easy.
来吧，很容易的

50
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:34,574
Look out, here I come.
小心，我来了

51
00:04:41,189 --> 00:04:42,382
Where's he gone?
他去哪儿了？

52
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,347
Over there.
在那边

53
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:53,424
What on Earth? Look!
这是什么？看！

54
00:04:53,778 --> 00:04:55,172
Blimey! What is it?
啊呀，那是什么？

55
00:04:55,968 --> 00:04:57,148
Doctor, what is it?
博士，它是什么？

56
00:04:57,795 --> 00:04:59,132
I don't know.
我不知道

57
00:04:59,324 --> 00:05:01,145
Hey, I can see Jamie, there he is.
嘿，我看见 Jamie 了，他在那儿

58
00:05:02,173 --> 00:05:03,813
Hey, there's somebody coming out.
嘿，有人出来了

59
00:05:04,571 --> 00:05:06,560
Come on, let's go.
快来，我们走

60
00:06:38,704 --> 00:06:40,494
What on Earth is it?
这究竟是怎么回事？

61
00:06:43,658 --> 00:06:47,354
I don't know. Get him along to the Medical unit.
我不知道．把他弄到医务室去

62
00:06:47,597 --> 00:06:49,537
But Doctor Evans has gone down with it as well.
但是 Evans 医生已经也因为这个病倒下了

63
00:06:49,772 --> 00:06:53,945
Yes, I know that. But the relief doctor from Earth
should be here on the next shuttle. Roger.
是的，我知道．但是地球派来救援的医生还得下个班次才能到这里，Roger

64
00:06:54,144 --> 00:06:55,697
Yes, of course. Bob, give me a hand, will you?
是的，当然. Bob, 搭把手，好吗？

65
00:06:55,961 --> 00:06:56,724
Yes, right.
好的，行

66
00:07:02,605 --> 00:07:05,454
And... Jules, you take over.
然后... Jules，你接手

67
00:07:07,778 --> 00:07:09,792
Come on, he won't bite you.
没事，他又不会咬你

68
00:07:12,341 --> 00:07:15,625
There must be some source to this infection./
这种感染一定有某种来源

69
00:07:15,741 --> 00:07:17,925
Look, get the lads in here and tell them what's happening. 
听着，那就把小伙子们叫进来，告诉他们发生了什么事

70
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:19,925
Get them on the blower will you, Nils.
把他们到鼓风机这边，好吧，Nils？

71
00:07:20,044 --> 00:07:21,002
Okay Nobby.
好的，老大

72
00:07:24,638 --> 00:07:30,442
Nils speaking. We, er... We got a bit of a flap on up here...
我是 Nils． 我们，呃..我们这里出现了一些情况...

73
00:07:34,432 --> 00:07:36,562
Mr. Hobson wants a word with you all...
Hobson 先生想给大家说明一下

74
00:07:36,799 --> 00:07:39,975
Hello. Where did you lot spring from? /
你好，你们是从哪里蹦出来的？

75
00:07:40,099 --> 00:07:42,975
Don't tell me the shuttle rocket arrived already?
别告诉我穿梭火箭已经到了？

76
00:07:43,084 --> 00:07:43,899
No, it hasn't.
不，它没有

77
00:07:44,101 --> 00:07:47,425
There was another one with them, sir.
Bob taken him along to the Medical unit.
他们还有一个人，头儿．Bob 已经将他带到医务室去了

78
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:49,925
He's all right. He's just knocked himself out or something.
他没大碍，只是自己撞到什么东西上了

79
00:07:50,121 --> 00:07:54,601
Oh no, if we haven't got enough troubles already.
They've been through the sterile room?
噢不，好像我们麻烦还不够多似的．他们已经经过消毒室了吧？

80
00:07:54,826 --> 00:07:55,394
Yes, Nobby.
好的，老大

81
00:07:55,606 --> 00:07:58,900
We don't want to cause you any trouble.
Just let us collect our young friend and we'll be off.
我们不会给你们添麻烦的．让我们去接我们的年轻朋友，然后我们就离开

82
00:07:59,151 --> 00:08:00,905
Hey, not so fast.
嘿，别这么着急

83
00:08:01,138 --> 00:08:02,806
Please let me go and see Jamie.
请让我走，我要去看看 Jamie

84
00:08:03,026 --> 00:08:06,759
I will take you there Mademoiselle. If you will come with me.
我带你去那里，小姐，请跟我来

85
00:08:06,985 --> 00:08:09,511
All right, young lady. You can carry on.
好吧，年轻女士，你可以去

86
00:08:09,795 --> 00:08:10,429
This way.
这边

87
00:08:11,297 --> 00:08:14,175
But I just like to have a word with you two.
但我还是要跟你们俩聊一聊

88
00:08:14,565 --> 00:08:17,127
You can do with a extra bactical check by the look of it.
看你们的样子，你们需要再进行一次细菌检查

89
00:08:17,318 --> 00:08:18,245
Bactical check?
细菌检查？

90
00:08:18,442 --> 00:08:19,203
That's what I said.
我就是这么说的

91
00:08:19,618 --> 00:08:20,225
Well, thanks.
哦，谢了

92
00:08:20,403 --> 00:08:22,771
I'll let you know that our TARDIS is as sterile...
我要告诉你我们的 TARDIS 是无菌的...

93
00:08:23,004 --> 00:08:23,660
TARDIS?

94
00:08:23,891 --> 00:08:24,913
Our space craft.
我们的宇宙飞船

95
00:08:25,188 --> 00:08:27,044
They're all here, sir. Any time you're ready.
他们都到了，头儿．你好了就可以开始

96
00:08:27,263 --> 00:08:30,304
Right. Well, we'll learn more about your spacecraft a little later./
好．那，我们过一小会儿在来详细了解你们的飞船

97
00:08:30,363 --> 00:08:33,704
Meanwhile, you better come along with me
and meet my team and listen to what I have to say.
与此同时，你们最好跟我过来，见一下我的团队，听听我要跟他们说的事情

98
00:08:33,903 --> 00:08:34,797
Thank you very much.
很是感谢

99
00:08:40,963 --> 00:08:42,584
Well, you know what this place is?
对了，你知道这是什么地方吗？

100
00:08:42,821 --> 00:08:47,464
Well, it looks like some sort of weather control centre.
这个嘛，看起来像是某种天气控制中心

101
00:08:47,663 --> 00:08:52,839
Ah, yes. And that's the thing with which
you control the weather. That's the culprit then.
啊，是的．那就是用来控制天气的东西．它那就是罪魁祸首了

102
00:08:53,225 --> 00:08:58,947
Hmmm. That's what gave us a bumpy landing.
Some sort of gravity device.
嗯，就是那东西让我们着陆时颠簸．某种引力装置

103
00:08:59,319 --> 00:09:04,903
Some sort of Gravity device?! You are from Earth aren't you?
"某种"引力装置? 你是从地球来的吧，是吗？

104
00:09:05,304 --> 00:09:06,045
Yes.
是的

105
00:09:06,355 --> 00:09:10,492
Well, where have you been for the past 20 years.
Every school kid knows about the Gravitron in there.
哦，过去２０年你都去哪儿了？每个孩子都知道这里的＂引力创＂

106
00:09:10,784 --> 00:09:15,692
Ah, yes. It must be about the year 2050，Ben.
啊，是了，这肯定是2050年，Ben

107
00:09:15,906 --> 00:09:18,219
We've got a proper Rip Van Winkle here.
我们碰到Rip Van Winkle本尊了
<i>（注: 美国作家华盛顿-欧文的同名短篇小说中的主角,
故事讲述一个美国村民在山上睡着了，醒来后发现已是２０年后，物是人非）</i>

108
00:09:19,336 --> 00:09:21,488
It's 2070，in case you like to know.
现在是 2070 年，如果你想知道的话

109
00:09:21,710 --> 00:09:24,324
There you are - I was only twenty years out.
看吧 - 我的偏差才２０年

110
00:09:24,524 --> 00:09:29,108
Well, before we all forget what century we're in,
I'd better tell you why I have called you here.
好吧，在我们都忘了我们在那个世纪之前，我最好告诉你为什么我把你们都叫过来

111
00:09:29,175 --> 00:09:32,186
Won't you introduce us first. I am a Doctor.
你不先介绍一下我们吗？我是个博士（医生）

112
00:09:32,921 --> 00:09:36,184
The Doctor? You're arrived just in time. We need your help.
医生？你还得真及时啊．我们需要你的帮助

113
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,166
Ah, do you?
啊，是吗？

114
00:09:37,385 --> 00:09:38,544
I'll see you in a moment.
我一会儿再找你

115
00:09:38,938 --> 00:09:40,691
Now, this virus...
现在，说说这个病毒...

116
00:09:40,941 --> 00:09:43,535
I may be able to help you if you introduce us.
如果你给我们介绍一下的话我也许能帮上忙

117
00:09:43,754 --> 00:09:46,231
Right, Doctor. You'd better meet them all./46.2
行，博士，你最好见一下他们

118
00:09:46,354 --> 00:09:50,631
We're all scientists you see.
No room for idle hands, I see to that. /50.6
你看，我们都是科学家．这里没有闲人，我确保了这一点

119
00:09:50,754 --> 00:09:53,631
Roger Benoit, beside you here, is my assistant. /53.5
Roger Benoit, 在你旁边的这位，是我的助手

120
00:09:53,754 --> 00:09:56,631
He takes over as Chief Scientist if anything happens to me.
如果我遭遇什么，他会接手成为首席科学家

121
00:09:56,848 --> 00:09:58,425
He's a physicist like me and Joe Bentsburg. /58.5
他跟我和 Joe Bentsburg 一样是个物理学家

122
00:09:58,648 --> 00:10:04,225
Nils, our mad Dane, is an astronomer
and mathematician as is Charlie here. /04.2
Nils, 我们疯狂的丹麦人，是一个宇航员，也跟这位 Charlie 一样是位数学家

123
00:10:04,348 --> 00:10:07,625
Ralph, Jules and Frances are geologists./07.6
Ralph, Jules 和 Frances 是地理学家

124
00:10:07,848 --> 00:10:11,225
When they are not acting as cooks, look-outs,
general... you know... handyman.
不过他们有时也是厨师＼瞭望员＼或者杂务工fixme

125
00:10:11,515 --> 00:10:14,468
And this is where you control the Earth's weather.
那这个就是你控制地球天气的地方

126
00:10:14,713 --> 00:10:15,584
Hm-Hmm.
嗯哼 

127
00:10:15,805 --> 00:10:16,688
I see.
我明白了

128
00:10:16,935 --> 00:10:21,353
The gravitron controls the tides,
the tides controls the weather.
引力创控制潮汐，潮汐就控制天气

129
00:10:21,472 --> 00:10:24,159
And from this console here we can plot it all on that map.
然后从这个控制台，我们可以将这一切绘制在那个地图上

130
00:10:25,017 --> 00:10:26,267
Simple, eh?
简单不？

131
00:10:26,461 --> 00:10:27,860
Yeah, very simple.
是，非常简单

132
00:10:29,454 --> 00:10:31,614
Wish we had this back in 1966.
真希望我们在 1966 年也有这个

133
00:10:32,034 --> 00:10:33,470
Why? Was it a bad year...
为什么？那年气候不好吗...

134
00:10:37,104 --> 00:10:41,253
It's Jim. Quick Francois, take over.
是 Jim．快点，Francois，你接手

135
00:10:53,696 --> 00:10:56,531
Cursor Five over the Pacific is starting to move.
太平洋上的第五游标开始移动

136
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:57,677
What does that mean?
那是什么意思？

137
00:10:57,968 --> 00:10:59,641
Some form of change in the weather.
天气会有某种变化了

138
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,456
We're soon hear from Earth what it means.
我们很快能从地球听到那是什么意思

139
00:11:01,646 --> 00:11:02,588
Here it comes!
来了

140
00:11:02,748 --> 00:11:07,717
International Space Control Earth calling
Weather Control Moon - come in please.
国际空间控制中心地球站呼叫天气控制中心月球站 - 听到请回答

141
00:11:07,907 --> 00:11:09,096
Moonport - standing by.
月球基地 正在待命

142
00:11:09,272 --> 00:11:11,781
Ever seen anything like that before, Doctor?
以前见过这样的情况吗，博士？

143
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:13,789
Hobson here.
Hobson 在呢

144
00:11:15,614 --> 00:11:18,984
What's happening up there? The hurricane you were guiding/
上面发生什么事了？你们所引导的飓风

145
00:11:19,014 --> 00:11:22,584
is now 45 degrees off course. It's threatening Hawaii.
现在偏离了45度．它正在威胁夏威夷

146
00:11:23,195 --> 00:11:26,443
One of my men were taken ill. We're operational again now.
我的一个手下生病了．我们已恢复运作

147
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:31,328
The controller would like to know the cause of the illness.
控制员想知道疾病的原因

148
00:11:31,584 --> 00:11:35,543
Yes, so would we. We now have three men down/35.5
是，我们也想知道．我们现在已经有三个人倒下了

149
00:11:35,584 --> 00:11:39,743
with this mysterious virus in the past few hours
- including the Doctor.
都是因为这种神秘的病毒，在过去的几小时内 -- 包括医生本人

150
00:11:40,266 --> 00:11:45,788
One moment please. Stand by for further instructions.
稍等一下，请等候进一步指示

151
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:49,247
Just hang on for another couple of minutes lads./49.2
再等几分钟，小伙子们

152
00:11:49,379 --> 00:11:52,447
We better hear what the great Mr. Rinberg has to say.
我们最好听听伟大的林伯格先生有什么话要说

153
00:11:52,714 --> 00:11:53,505
Nobby?
老大?

154
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:54,307
Yes.
什么事?

155
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,682
There it is again. I'll play it back to you.
又出现了，我回放给你

156
00:11:56,968 --> 00:12:04,994
"Yes, so would we. We now have three men down
with this mysterious virus in the past few hours
- including the Doctor. "
"是，我们也想知道．我们现在已经有三个人倒下了..."

157
00:12:06,236 --> 00:12:12,864
"One moment please. Stand by for further instructions. "
"稍等一下，请等候进一步指示"

158
00:12:13,457 --> 00:12:18,392
Here the big noise ratio on that re-run.
We're being monitored again.
重放时可以听到里面有很大的噪声．我们又被监听了

159
00:12:18,642 --> 00:12:19,643
Monitored?
监听？

160
00:12:19,937 --> 00:12:25,584
Someone, not too far away from the base,
is listening to every word we say.
某个人，正在离基地不远的地方，监听着我们说的每一个字

161
00:12:27,495 --> 00:12:32,348
"Moonbase, Moonbase, come in Moonbase. "
月球基地，月球基地，收到请回话

162
00:12:32,594 --> 00:12:34,176
Still standing by.
还在待命呢

163
00:12:49,812 --> 00:12:50,591
Well?
怎样？

164
00:12:52,369 --> 00:12:57,235
Your instruction's to send blood samples back
to Earth for investigation.
对你们的指示是把血样送回地球进行检查

165
00:13:00,864 --> 00:13:03,821
Well, when can we do that? The next shuttle rocket's
not for another month.
那，我们什么时候做这个？下一班穿梭火箭还得一个月吧

166
00:13:05,486 --> 00:13:11,157
Then they must be put on that rocket.
In the meantime the Moonbase is to put into quarantine.
那就得放在那一班火箭上，再次期间月球基地必须进行隔离

167
00:13:11,392 --> 00:13:17,851
Quarantine! What if these men aren't fit enough
to get back to work. I shall need replacements.
隔离？如果这些人没法恢复到可以工作怎么办？我需要替补啊

168
00:13:18,203 --> 00:13:21,399
If you radio information about this virus,/21
如果你将这种病毒的信息传送过来,

169
00:13:21,403 --> 00:13:24,899
we can do our best to identify it and suggest treatment.
我们可以尽最大努力识别它，并给出治疗建议

170
00:13:24,949 --> 00:13:27,274
I demand to speak to Rinberg.
我请求与Rinberg 对话

171
00:13:29,755 --> 00:13:34,690
The controller is busy - I'm sorry. Over and out.
控制员正忙，对不起．结束通话

172
00:13:36,653 --> 00:13:41,832
That whole conversion was monitored by someone or something.
整个通话过程都被监听了，被某个人或某种东西

173
00:13:41,906 --> 00:13:45,460
Oh, never mind about that now.
That Rinberg fellow just won't talk to you.
哦，现在别管那个了．Rinberg 那个家伙不会和你说话的

174
00:13:45,806 --> 00:13:49,860
How can we trace down this mystery illness
with the Doctor himself down with it.
我们怎样才能追查出这种神秘的疾病的来源呢，我们的医生都被他干倒了

175
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:54,101
We better get out of these things and see how Jamie is.
Perhaps I can be of help in the sick bay now.
我们最好先抽身去看看 Jamie 怎么样了．也许现在我可以在医务室帮上点忙

176
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:55,652
Anything you can do... Bob!
能做些什么就做吧...Bob！

177
00:13:55,908 --> 00:13:57,095
Yes, Mr Hobson?
什么，Hobson 先生？

178
00:13:57,264 --> 00:13:58,804
Show them to the Medical unit will you?
带他们去医务室，可以吗？

179
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,031
Yes, of course. Now, if you will come this way, please?
好的，当然．现在，你们来这边吧，请

180
00:14:01,217 --> 00:14:02,984
Yes. Thank you.
好．谢谢你

181
00:14:05,459 --> 00:14:06,962
Well, you all heard the position.
好了，当前的情况你们都听到了．

182
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:10,962
We don't know what this infection is
and how it got into the base
我们不知道这种传染病是什么，是怎么进到基地的

183
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:14,962
but I want you all to take extra precautions
while this emergency is on
但当前还是紧急状态，我期望你们都千万小心

184
00:14:15,459 --> 00:14:17,562
We may be short-handed for quite a while.
我们在相当一段时间内可能会人手不足TS

185
00:14:18,279 --> 00:14:19,492
Is this how its goes, Doctor?
它就是这样运作的吗，博士？

186
00:14:20,424 --> 00:14:25,517
Yes, that's right. Then, this unit automatically
controls the pulse, the temperature and the breathing.
对，就是那样．然后，这个设备会自动控制脉搏、体温和呼吸

187
00:14:26,013 --> 00:14:27,371
A sort of electronic Doctor.
像是个电子医生

188
00:14:27,580 --> 00:14:30,220
Yes. Almost got stripe trousers.
是的，几乎可以帮忙脱裤子了

189
00:14:30,402 --> 00:14:31,942
And it even give you medicines too?
而且它还能给配药吗？

190
00:14:32,114 --> 00:14:33,998
Yes. It will do very nearly everything.
是的，它差不多能干所有事

191
00:14:34,254 --> 00:14:38,077
Can't be nice to him. How do you think he is, Doctor?
这太适合他了．你觉得他状态怎么样，博士？

192
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:42,902
Oh, he's not too bad. He's a bit concussed
and feverish but he'll be all right with rest.
哦，并不差．他有点脑震荡和发烧，但休息一下就没事了

193
00:14:42,957 --> 00:14:47,571
The Piper! The McCrimmon Piper! Don't let him get me!
风笛手！McCrimmon家的风笛手！别让他抓走我！

194
00:14:47,754 --> 00:14:48,656
Piper?
风笛手？

195
00:14:49,874 --> 00:14:55,944
Some legend of his clan. As far, as I can make out
- this piper appears to a McCrimmon just before he dies.
他们家族的某个传说．据我了解，McCrimmon 家族的人死之前这个风笛手就会出现

196
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,959
Has this phantom piper appeared to Jamie yet?
那这个幽灵风笛手在 Jaime 面前出现了吗？

197
00:14:59,239 --> 00:15:00,578
You don't believe it, do you?
你不会相信这个吧，会吗？

198
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:02,964
No, but he does. It's important to him.
不信，但他信，这对他很重要

199
00:15:03,179 --> 00:15:05,622
He keeps asking us to keep the piper away from him.
他不停地要求我们不让那个风笛手靠近他

200
00:15:05,834 --> 00:15:08,966
Good. We can see if we can do just that.
好，我们看看能不能做到

201
00:15:11,170 --> 00:15:12,426
Well, carry on Nurse.
好了，继续吧护士

202
00:15:12,655 --> 00:15:17,741
Well, at least I try to help. There's a ward full of sick men
and no doctor. Somebody got to do something.
嗯，至少我会尽量帮忙．这里满是病人，没有医生，得有人做点什么

203
00:15:21,304 --> 00:15:22,365
I wonder who this is?
咦，这是谁？

204
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:25,696
Don't get too near. Have a look on his chart.
别太近了，看看他的记录

205
00:15:25,938 --> 00:15:27,455
That's a good idea.
这是个好注意

206
00:15:27,672 --> 00:15:28,707
It's Dr. Evans.
是 Evans 医生

207
00:15:28,893 --> 00:15:31,647
Oh, yes. The station doctor. He was the first one to get it.
哦，对，站内的医生．他是第一个得病的

208
00:15:31,849 --> 00:15:33,414
He looks one of the worst.
他是看起来情况最严重的

209
00:15:33,649 --> 00:15:38,760
There's something about this epidemic
that I... I just don't understand. 
对于这个流行病，有一些是我...不能理解的

210
00:15:38,849 --> 00:15:42,760
It's not like a real disease at all! It's almost just...
看着就不像一种真正的疾病，完全像是...

211
00:15:42,846 --> 00:15:44,490
Not real! What more do you want?
不是真正的！你还想要多真？

212
00:15:44,669 --> 00:15:48,860
I don't know. But there are certain signs and symptoms
which don't add up.
我不知道，但这里有一些体征和症状相互矛盾

213
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:53,124
Ben, I want you to go to the control room and keep an eye on things.
Ben，我要你到控制室去，盯着点

214
00:15:53,359 --> 00:15:54,103
But how?
怎么盯？

215
00:15:54,303 --> 00:15:57,220
Give a hand, do anything but keep your eyes and ears open.
帮帮忙什么的，做什么都行，不过眼睛要放亮点

216
00:15:57,464 --> 00:15:58,304
Right.
好

217
00:15:58,325 --> 00:16:01,697
There's something very wrong here. Something very wrong indeed.
这里有些事情非常不对劲，真的非常不对劲

218
00:16:08,064 --> 00:16:12,173
Still up, Nobby. Why not take a rest. Go and get some sleep.
还没睡啊，Nobby, 为什么不休息一下，去睡一下吧

219
00:16:12,464 --> 00:16:17,544
Oh, How can I rest with that thing up the spout.
You know the score as well as I do.
噢，有了这事儿我这么还能睡得着啊，你跟我一样清楚现在的状态

220
00:16:17,564 --> 00:16:21,444
Five units off centre and we lift half London into space!
偏离中心五个单位，半个伦敦就被抬到空中了

221
00:16:21,464 --> 00:16:24,944
Five more and the Atlantic water level goes up three feet! 
再偏五个单位，大西洋的水平面就得上升三尺！

222
00:16:25,014 --> 00:16:28,244
Rinberg don't understand the pressure we're under.
Rinerg 并不理解我们当前的压力

223
00:16:28,246 --> 00:16:31,807
Hey you! What do you thinking you are doing?! Skulking here?
嘿你！你在干什么呢！在这里躲懒吗?

224
00:16:32,002 --> 00:16:34,500
Well I was just wondering if I can help, sir.
喔，我只是在看有什么能帮上忙的，先生

225
00:16:34,710 --> 00:16:35,874
Help? how can you help?
帮忙，你能帮什么忙？

226
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:38,380
We can do with an extra pair of hands - he can help me.
我们这边需要多几个人手 - 他可以来帮我

227
00:16:38,573 --> 00:16:40,475
Well, keep him away from me, that's all.
行，别让他在我这里晃悠就行了．

228
00:16:40,573 --> 00:16:43,275
All right, I'll go and lie down. Call me if anything happens.
好了，我走了，去躺躺．如果有任何事就叫我

229
00:16:43,380 --> 00:16:44,250
Yes, of course.
好的，当然

230
00:16:44,457 --> 00:16:49,161
Oh, by the way, there were two more of those momentary drops
in air pressure while I was on.
哦，顺便说一下，我在这里的时候又出现过两次短暂的气压下降

231
00:16:49,257 --> 00:16:50,161
I have put them in the log.
我都记在日志里面了

232
00:16:50,470 --> 00:16:51,207
Right.
好的

233
00:16:53,614 --> 00:16:57,476
Well, there are some coffee cups to clear away
if you want to be helpful. And.../
对了，有一些咖啡杯需要收走 - 如果你想帮着做点什么．另外...

234
00:16:57,614 --> 00:17:03,476
Oh and Ralph, no. 14，needs a hand down in the food store.
Can you find your way there?
哦，另外 Ralph - 14号 - 那边食物储藏间需要人搭把手．你能找到那里吧？
<i>（注：你注意到他们每位员工的衣服上都有编号了吗）</i>

235
00:17:03,497 --> 00:17:04,237
I'll find it.
我能找到

236
00:17:04,368 --> 00:17:05,203
Good boy.
棒小伙

237
00:17:39,626 --> 00:17:41,749
Anyone would think we got rats up here.
谁会想到这里还会有老鼠

238
00:17:48,498 --> 00:17:49,488
Who's that?!
谁在那儿！

239
00:17:56,072 --> 00:17:57,184
WHO IS THAT?!
谁在那儿？

240
00:17:57,617 --> 00:17:58,791
Only me, mate.
是我，朋友

241
00:17:59,224 --> 00:18:02,852
Oh, for heaven's sake. Don't go sneaking about like that!
哦，天啊，你不要这样悄无声息地走进来

242
00:18:03,076 --> 00:18:04,677
Blimey! You lot aren't half edgy.
啊呀！你们这些人不是有一点急躁啊

243
00:18:04,896 --> 00:18:07,665
You would be too, mate, if you have been up here long enough.
你也会的，朋友，只要你在这里呆得够久

244
00:18:08,647 --> 00:18:12,499
Say, are you responsible for the broken bags here.
嗯，这些袋子破了是不是你造成的？

245
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:15,886
Come off it, I only just arrived, haven't I?
得了，我刚到这里，不是吗

246
00:18:15,971 --> 00:18:21,565
Okay. See and you can find that lamp.
Round the back, most likely.
好吧．你看看能不能找到灯．就在后面，，好像

247
00:18:21,604 --> 00:18:22,705
Okay.
好

248
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:35,247
Let's see. Still need some more... Milk and Sugar.
我来看看，还需要一些...牛奶和糖

249
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:55,029
No.14. Ralph!
14号 Ralph!

250
00:18:59,062 --> 00:19:00,458
Where are you?
你在哪儿？

251
00:19:03,797 --> 00:19:05,812
Scarpered. Funny bloke.
跑掉了，有趣的家伙

252
00:19:08,842 --> 00:19:09,864
What is that?
什么东西？

253
00:19:09,986 --> 00:19:15,039
Shhhh, it's all right Polly. It's only me./13.3
We don't want to wake everybody up do we?
嘘，没事的 Polly．就我一个．我们不想吵醒每一个人吧

254
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:24,650
You look if you can do with some sleep yourself.
你看起来也需要睡一会儿

255
00:19:24,959 --> 00:19:27,795
I'm all right.
我没事

256
00:19:28,554 --> 00:19:29,878
What have you got there?
你那边发现什么了吗？

257
00:19:30,109 --> 00:19:32,268
Oh, I been doing a little investigation.
哦，我做了一点调查

258
00:19:32,884 --> 00:19:34,439
A piece of silver paper. What is it?
一小块银箔，是什么东西？

259
00:19:34,659 --> 00:19:35,598
I don't know.
我不知道

260
00:19:36,331 --> 00:19:37,724
What's happened?!
什么情况？

261
00:19:37,983 --> 00:19:40,961
Oh, it's nothing. It probably just a changeover in the time cycle.
哦，没事．只是人工昼夜交替而已

262
00:19:41,370 --> 00:19:42,528
What do you mean?
什么意思？

263
00:19:42,825 --> 00:19:45,324
Oh, you see - it's rather interesting really
哦，你看，这真的很有意思

264
00:19:45,425 --> 00:19:49,324
you see on the moon, they have a fortnight of days
and a fortnight of nights.
你看，在月球上，他们有长达１４天的白天和１４天的黑夜

265
00:19:49,548 --> 00:19:50,292
Well?
是吗？

266
00:19:50,663 --> 00:19:56,209
Well, it's oblivious isn't it? They have to
make their own day and night artificially up there
是啊，这很明显啊是不？他们这里就不得不靠人工制造白天和黑夜

267
00:19:56,263 --> 00:19:59,809
Or it would upset their own biological time clock.
否则他们的生物钟就会紊乱

268
00:20:00,068 --> 00:20:01,084
Their what?
他们的什么？

269
00:20:01,349 --> 00:20:04,586
They won't know if they were coming or going. Get it?
他们就不知道该起床还是睡觉了，明白了吗？

270
00:20:04,847 --> 00:20:05,733
Yes.
哦

271
00:20:06,123 --> 00:20:08,835
Clever girl. QED. That's why it's dark up here.
聪明. 证明完毕．这就是为什么现在这里黑了

272
00:20:09,553 --> 00:20:12,787
Oh, I see what you mean. Yes, of course. How stupid of me.
哦，我明白你什么意思了．对了，当然．我真是太蠢了

273
00:20:12,993 --> 00:20:15,824
Of course along the control centre it's probably broad daylight.
当然了在控制中心那边可能一直都是白天

274
00:20:16,649 --> 00:20:18,903
Polly, you wouldn't be making fun of me would you?
Polly, 你不是在逗我吧，是吗？

275
00:20:19,453 --> 00:20:20,167
No.
不！

276
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:21,482
Dr. Evans.
Evans 医生

277
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:38,581
The hand. No, don't touch me. No. The silver hand.
手，不，不要碰我．不要，银色的手

278
00:20:50,119 --> 00:20:51,855
Doctor, is he...
博士，他是不是．．．

279
00:20:53,904 --> 00:20:56,592
Yes, I'm afraid he is.
是的，恐怕他是

280
00:21:05,319 --> 00:21:06,728
What are we gone to do?
那我们该做什么？

281
00:21:06,939 --> 00:21:11,798
What does he means by the silver hand.
I better report this to Mr. Hobson.
他说＂银色的手＂是什么意思？我最好向 Hobson 先生报告一下

282
00:21:18,948 --> 00:21:20,896
Can't find him! Ralph!?
找不到他了？是说 Ralph？

283
00:21:21,103 --> 00:21:24,075
Well, I was helping him load some stores
and he just disappeared.
嗯，我正在帮他整理储藏，他就不见了

284
00:21:24,159 --> 00:21:27,019
What! In this place. Well, there are only nineteen of us.
什么？！就这么大点地方，我们就只有19个人

285
00:21:27,184 --> 00:21:28,556
Have you tried his quarters?
你去他的房间找过吗？

286
00:21:28,758 --> 00:21:29,294
Yes.
找过

287
00:21:29,516 --> 00:21:30,872
Why didn't you report this to me?
你当时怎么不向我报告呢？

288
00:21:31,064 --> 00:21:32,506
Well, I just telling you now, aren't I?
我不是现在在跟你说吗，是吧？

289
00:21:32,684 --> 00:21:33,557
What is it now?
现在什么情况？fixme

290
00:21:33,743 --> 00:21:35,031
Terribly sorry. It's Dr. Evans.
可怕的事，是 Evans 医生

291
00:21:35,213 --> 00:21:35,912
Well?
怎么

292
00:21:36,161 --> 00:21:37,283
I'm afraid he's dead.
恐怕他是死了

293
00:21:37,507 --> 00:21:41,293
Dead? No.
死了？不

294
00:21:41,623 --> 00:21:43,344
This must be reported at once.
这事必须得立刻汇报

295
00:21:44,019 --> 00:21:47,830
Yes, yes... No! No, we haven't got enough data yet.
是啊是啊...不！不，我们还没有足够的数据

296
00:21:48,119 --> 00:21:49,830
You know what they're like down there.
你知道下面那些人是怎样的

297
00:21:49,919 --> 00:21:52,630
I'll come to the sick bay with you. Come on.
我现在就跟你去医务室．来吧

298
00:21:57,427 --> 00:21:58,439
Here.
这里

299
00:21:59,294 --> 00:22:01,302
Gently, Jamie.
慢点，Jamie

300
00:22:09,962 --> 00:22:11,149
Jamie!

301
00:22:28,368 --> 00:22:29,315
What's the matter?
什么情况？

302
00:22:29,536 --> 00:22:31,439
Something just went out of that door!
什么东西从那个门跑出去了！

303
00:22:31,641 --> 00:22:32,927
Nils! John!

304
00:22:34,396 --> 00:22:35,461
What was it?
是什么东西？

305
00:22:41,062 --> 00:22:43,040
Nothing. Nothing there.
没有，那里什么也没有

306
00:22:49,711 --> 00:22:53,105
Your nerves are getting the better of you.
Where's Evan's body?
你太神经过敏了．Evan 的尸体呢？

307
00:22:53,557 --> 00:22:54,331
Over there.
在那边

308
00:23:01,876 --> 00:23:04,212
All right, let's get it over with.
好了，让我们结束吧

309
00:23:09,875 --> 00:23:13,489
Is this someone's idea of a particularly bad joke?
这是哪个家伙开的恶意玩笑吗？

310
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:14,595
This is no joke, believe me!
这不是玩笑，相信我！

311
00:23:14,766 --> 00:23:16,766
Mr. Hobson, Mr. Hobson, you are wanted!
Hobson 先生，Hobson 先生，这里需要你

312
00:23:17,066 --> 00:23:20,166
Another man's collapsed at the controls
and the Gravitron has been thrown off alignment again.
控制室又有一个人倒下了，引力创也又一次跑偏了

313
00:23:20,257 --> 00:23:20,900
Come on!
快来！

314
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:28,273
And you better find that Doctor's body or out you all go
- quarantine or no quarantine.
你们最好找到医生的尸体，否则你们都得出去 - 不管隔离不隔离

315
00:23:31,148 --> 00:23:35,712
I don't understand what could have happened.
I must have dozed off or something
我不清楚刚才可能发生了什么，我肯定是打盹了

316
00:23:35,848 --> 00:23:39,562
but one thing I am sure of
- something went out of that door just as you came in.
但有一件事我可以肯定：你进来的时候有什么东西跑出那个门去了

317
00:23:39,611 --> 00:23:44,190
That body can't just have vanished.
Polly, I am going to leave you alone...
尸体不可能凭空消失的．Polly, 我得让你一个人在这里...

318
00:23:44,309 --> 00:23:45,266
...just for a minute.
...就几分钟

319
00:23:45,895 --> 00:23:46,699
All right.
好的

320
00:23:47,145 --> 00:23:50,012
Water. Water.
水．水

321
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,043
I'll go and get you some.
我去给你弄点

322
00:23:52,254 --> 00:23:53,371
Water!
水！

323
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:30,000
It's you, the phantom piper!
是你，幽灵风笛手！

